# ─── P1-9 (audit 2026-05-08): personal infra outside public surface ──
# `internal/` is the parking lot for files that mirror operator-specific
# deployment (compose with personal IPs/paths, profiling launch scripts
# tied to specific NUMA topology, etc.). Public repo ships only generic
# templates in `compose/` and `scripts/` — anything operator-specific
# moves here.
internal/

# ─── P0-5 (audit 2026-05-08): protect commercial engine boundary ──────
# vllm/sndr_engine/ is the COMMERCIAL package. Ignoring it locally
# prevents accidental `git add .` from publishing private kernels +
# patch wiring to the public Apache repo.
#
# For a real release: move sndr_engine to a SEPARATE private repo
# entirely. This .gitignore rule is defense-in-depth, not the primary
# boundary.
vllm/sndr_engine/
pyproject-engine.toml

# Audit / plan files at repo root (also catches sndr_*_audit_*.md)
sndr_*_audit_*.md
sndr_*_plan_*.md
sndr_repeat_*.md

